    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-09-11T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-09-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="121"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.75/31: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Aldridge</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-11T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 11, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Your 76, August 31, 6 p.m.<note n="39" xml:id="d121fn39">Not printed.</note>
                    Since the International Telephone and Telegraph Corporation, largely because the
                    Greek Minister of Communications desired it (as was reported in your 39, May 25,
                    1 p.m., and 41, May 28, 6 p.m.), went to the trouble and the expense originally
                    of presenting a bid, the Department hopes the Greek Government will afford an
                    opportunity to the corporation to compete for the telephone contract at the
                    present time on a basis of equality with the other interested firms.</p>
                <p>The foregoing should be brought by you to the attention of the appropriate
                    authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
